node.text:
It’s no secret that I haven’t been my best the past few years. Poor choices, immaturity, and injuries led me into some serious depression. In the video I explain, how @transcendhrt has played a huge roll in helping me bounce back! If this video sparks any interest of your own, be sure to go fill out a client intake form at www.TranscendCompany.com
-
As long as you are over 18 & in the US. They can help you like they’ve helped me.
-
20% off code is in my bio.

node.title: I was at my worst & now I’m building myself back up again!

node.text:
It’s no secret that I haven’t been my best the past few years. Poor choices, immaturity, and injuries led me into some serious depression. In the video I explain, how @transcendhrt has played a huge roll in helping me bounce back! If this video sparks any interest of your own, be sure to go fill out a client intake form at www.TranscendCompany.com
-
As long as you are over 18 & in the US. They can help you like they’ve helped me.
-
20% off code is in my bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jeremy L. Buendia on August 19, 2021 tagging @stasia_buendia_. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text:
My Wife ❤️
-
I’ve known you forever and been around the world just to find my way back home to you.
-
You are the one who has changed me. The one who has shown me the true meaning of love and life.
-
I realize how blessed I am to have you. You understand me better than anyone and you love me in a way that no one ever has. You put Eliana and I first & always do your best to make me feel good about myself.
-
The way you love and mother our child, I couldn’t ask for any one better. @stasia_buendia_ I love you, you stood strong for me when I wasn’t able too, and you’ve been my rock during some of the hardest times of my life.
-
I love you forever ❤️

node.text:
Had to call an extra set of eyes to analyze my progress.
-
Baby Eliana gave me the approval, & she told me up the calories.
-
It’s funny every time I pose she gets a kick out of it! ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jeremy L. Buendia on August 17, 2021 tagging @yavalabs. May be an image of 1 person, biceps and beard.

node.text:
The goal is to be a little better everyday. Not allowing “off-days” to knock me off track. Consistent incremental progress adds up. 8 weeks ago, I didn’t look good enough to post a pic with my shirt off, and here I am today.
-
A lot can happen in a short time if you put your mind to it. Can’t wait to see what I’ll look like in another 8 weeks.
-
@yavalabs
